#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:108
msgid ""
"Given a sample `a` from an underlying distribution, `quantile` provides a "
"nonparametric estimate of the inverse cumulative distribution function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:111
msgid ""
"By default, this is done by interpolating between adjacent elements in "
"``y``, a sorted copy of `a`::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:114
msgid "(1-g)*y[j] + g*y[j+1]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:116
msgid ""
"where the index ``j`` and coefficient ``g`` are the integral and fractional "
"components of ``q * (n-1)``, and ``n`` is the number of elements in the "
"sample."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:120
msgid ""
"This is a special case of Equation 1 of H&F [Re01cd3f3acfe-1]_. More "
"generally,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:122
msgid "``j = (q*n + m - 1) // 1``, and"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:123
msgid "``g = (q*n + m - 1) % 1``,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:125
msgid ""
"where ``m`` may be defined according to several different conventions. The "
"preferred convention may be selected using the ``method`` parameter:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:129
msgid "``method``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:129
msgid "number in H&F"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:129
msgid "``m``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:131
msgid "``interpolated_inverted_cdf``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:131
msgid "4"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:131
msgid "``0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:132
msgid "``hazen``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:132
msgid "5"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:132
msgid "``1/2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:133
msgid "``weibull``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:133
msgid "6"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:133
msgid "``q``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:134
msgid "``linear`` (default)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:134
msgid "7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:134
msgid "``1 - q``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:135
msgid "``median_unbiased``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:135
msgid "8"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:135
msgid "``q/3 + 1/3``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:136
msgid "``normal_unbiased``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:136
msgid "9"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:136
msgid "``q/4 + 3/8``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:139
msgid ""
"Note that indices ``j`` and ``j + 1`` are clipped to the range ``0`` to ``n "
"- 1`` when the results of the formula would be outside the allowed range of "
"non-negative indices. The ``- 1`` in the formulas for ``j`` and ``g`` "
"accounts for Python's 0-based indexing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:144
msgid ""
"The table above includes only the estimators from H&F that are continuous "
"functions of probability `q` (estimators 4-9). NumPy also provides the three "
"discontinuous estimators from H&F (estimators 1-3), where ``j`` is defined "
"as above, ``m`` is defined as follows, and ``g`` is a function of the real-"
"valued ``index = q*n + m - 1`` and ``j``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:150
msgid "``inverted_cdf``: ``m = 0`` and ``g = int(index - j > 0)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:151
msgid ""
"``averaged_inverted_cdf``: ``m = 0`` and ``g = (1 + int(index - j > 0)) / 2``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:153
msgid ""
"``closest_observation``: ``m = -1/2`` and ``g = 1 - int((index == j) & (j%2 "
"== 1))``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:156
msgid ""
"For backward compatibility with previous versions of NumPy, `quantile` "
"provides four additional discontinuous estimators. Like ``method='linear'``, "
"all have ``m = 1 - q`` so that ``j = q*(n-1) // 1``, but ``g`` is defined as "
"follows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:161
msgid "``lower``: ``g = 0``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:162
msgid "``midpoint``: ``g = 0.5``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:163
msgid "``higher``: ``g = 1``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:164
msgid "``nearest``: ``g = (q*(n-1) % 1) > 0.5``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:166
msgid ""
"**Weighted quantiles:** More formally, the quantile at probability level :"
"math:`q` of a cumulative distribution function :math:`F(y)=P(Y \\leq y)` "
"with probability measure :math:`P` is defined as any number :math:`x` that "
"fulfills the *coverage conditions*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:172
msgid ""
"P(Y < x) \\leq q \\quad\\text{and}\\quad P(Y \\leq x) \\geq q\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:174
msgid ""
"with random variable :math:`Y\\sim P`. Sample quantiles, the result of "
"`quantile`, provide nonparametric estimation of the underlying population "
"counterparts, represented by the unknown :math:`F`, given a data vector `a` "
"of length ``n``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:179
msgid ""
"Some of the estimators above arise when one considers :math:`F` as the "
"empirical distribution function of the data, i.e. :math:`F(y) = \\frac{1}{n} "
"\\sum_i 1_{a_i \\leq y}`. Then, different methods correspond to different "
"choices of :math:`x` that fulfill the above coverage conditions. Methods "
"that follow this approach are ``inverted_cdf`` and ``averaged_inverted_cdf``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.quantile:186
msgid ""
"For weighted quantiles, the coverage conditions still hold. The empirical "
"cumulative distribution is simply replaced by its weighted version, i.e. :"
"math:`P(Y \\leq t) = \\frac{1}{\\sum_i w_i} \\sum_i w_i 1_{x_i \\leq t}`. "
"Only ``method=\"inverted_cdf\"`` supports weights."
msgstr ""

